Gerbera is a UPnP media server which allows you to stream your digital media
through your home network and consume it on a variety of UPnP compatible devices.

## Features
* Browse and playback your media via your network on all kinds of devices.
* Web UI with a tree view of the database and the file system,
  allowing to add/remove/edit/browse your media
* Metadata extraction from MP3, OGG, AAC, M4A, FLAC, wavpack,
  JPG (and many more!) files.
* Media thumbnail support
* Highly flexible media format transcoding via plugins / scripts
* Automatic directory rescans (timed, inotify)
* User defined server layout based on extracted metadata
* Supports last.fm scrobbing
* On the fly video thumbnail generation
* Support for external URLs (create links to internet content
  and serve them via UPnP to your renderer)

